title: Painted
body:
Warning: so fluffy you could die

A/N: i’m also super self conscious without my makeup so i found this super relatable..

The door clicked softly behind you as you entered your room. You let out along sigh of relief while rubbing your face. Your skin felt so much lighter without any makeup.

“Hi, Y/N!” A voice caused you to jump. You noticed the red-haired boy on your bed. He stared at you with a wide smile on his face. Oh no. Your face now felt naked instead of light. “Kiri! What are you doing here?!! How did you get in!!” You exclaimed as you pivoted away from him. You crossed your arms. You wanted to be small.

The bed squeaked as he stood up from it. His steps got louder as he moved closer. “Your mom let me in. We were going to study today, remember?” You had completely forgotten about it. You shouldn’t have taken of your makeup. You squeezed your arms lightly, “oh yeah.. studying.”

“Hey,” he placed his hand on your shoulder softly, “is something wrong.. why won’t you look at me?” The sadness in his voice was almost unbearable.

“No, Kiri, it’s not you.. it’s just.. it’s kinda stupid but I don’t like how I look without makeup and I don’t want you to see me like this.” You tried to turn away from him. He stepped in front of you. You didn’t dare look up at him.

“Y/N, I know it’s probably hard for you to be around me without your makeup… so if you want me to wait for you to put some on I will.. but I want you to know I think you’re beautiful either way. And… and I don’t expect you to get all dressed up for me. I want you to feel comfortable in your own skin around me.” He placed his hands on both your shoulders and squeezed them firmly.

“Kiri, your so sweet.” You glanced up at the boy. His smile never faltered as he took in your “new” appearance. He leaned down and placed a soft kiss on your lips, “just for you.”

summary: Pre-Orders are now OPEN Apologies for the wait, but The Year of Heroes is excited to announce that our pre-orders have launched!...
caption:
Pre-Orders are now OPEN

Apologies for the wait, but The Year of Heroes is excited to announce that our pre-orders have launched! The Year of Heroes is a beautiful 11.5x8.5 inch wall calendar filled with art of our favorite kids. Our amazing artists drew 13 different scenarios of our beloved heroes performing the sort of heroic activities we can all do: Community Service.

From soup kitchens to racing for awareness to volunteering at a pet shelter, this calendar shows the more pedestrian but not any less important side of heroism.

To celebrate our shop opening and Veterans Day, we will be having a 10% off sale for today until 11:59 pm PST.

Pre-orders run from November 12 to December 12. Don’t miss out!

Pre-Order Here

Each sale of this calendar will help us do our own act of heroism, as the profits from The Year Of Heroes will be donated the Carter Center. The Carter Center is the former US President Jimmy Carter’s foundation, which focuses on raising the quality of life in more than 80 countries through campaigning for stronger democracies and human rights, solving conflicts, raising mental health awareness and much, much more.

Get your calendar today, enjoy the beautiful art, and help us help the world!
